<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="T" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Thievery" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Thievery,</orth> 1) theft: <cit><quote>it's an honourable kind of t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.1.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. IV, 1, 40</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>I'll example you with t.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.438" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 438</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) that which is stolen: <cit><quote>crams his rich t. up,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 4.4.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 4, 45</bibl></cit>.
